From the Philippines to the wide world, or Straw Bag trip to the heart of fashion fans
Bags woven from straws are a summer classic, which has become a hit product in its own right in recent years, which must be hanging on the arm of a true summer lover, and despite its humble origin, merchants have been able to attach a price tag appropriate to the hit.
A bag woven from straws is probably one of those things that have existed at least once in life and the possession of which has not caused special emotions.
It&#39;s just there, and if it&#39;s not, nothing&#39;s broken.
Now, however, straw bags are making a real comeback, and fashion fans have swapped their fancy designer bags for simple straw-woven bags for the summer months.
At the same time, it is not only a beach bag, but today it is just as popular as a street bag, and bolder women even walk with it to the office.
At this point, however, it is worth clarifying first whether a summer look like this for the boss still suits or if it is still worth pushing the notebook and laptop into a slightly more formal sumadan.
However, the versatility has made straw bags a true summer love of women.
For example, when reading foreign fashion blogs, the first thing that catches your eye is that fashion connoisseurs rush to the local market first thing on vacation and buy themselves a straw bag, which they stick with for the entire vacation and which goes with them on the beach, in the market, and when hanging out with girlfriends in the city.
Some bloggers are even so generous that they buy a large batch of bags from the market and sell or give them away to their loyal readers.
At the same time, it is worth noting that the demand for bags among readers is so great that in the real world, women (and men!) would probably go hand-in-hand with each other to become the lucky owner of a bag.
In a way, this kind of madness is also understandable, because it is rare in the world of fashion when you can buy something that has become a hit for just a few tens of euros.
It&#39;s true, cunning merchants have also discovered an easy way to make money here, and finer luxury brands sell straw bags for a few hundred and thousands of euros.
Probably still so that richer customers don&#39;t have to feel like mere mortals walking around with some cheap bags.
For example, it is possible to buy yourself a Dolce &amp; Gabbana straw bag costing over a thousand euros.
However, the interpretation of a Chanel straw bag can cost around 6,000 euros.
However, unlike most fashion hits, straw bags do not come from some big fashion house, but their story began much further back.
Namely, straw bags are said to come from far away in the Philippines, where they have been widely distributed.
Straw bag weaving is primarily an export business there, and you don&#39;t see locals walking around with them very often.
The straw weaving technique is said to date back to the 14th century and is quite similar to regular basket weaving.
However, since a straw bag does not have to be braided as tightly as a basket, patterns and other materials can be woven into them, which make the bag more personal and even more attractive.
For example, bags with colored ribbons or leather strips woven into them are particularly trendy recently.
Straw bags can especially send a letter of thanks to the actress Jane Birkin, the biggest fan of braided straw bags has never been seen before.
Namely, he matched the straw bag with all kinds of clothing sets and didn&#39;t think much of going to the Cannes Film Festival with it.
The fact that taking care of them is a piece of cake plays no small role in the popularity of the bags today, and unlike all other sumadas, they do not need to be cared for with special tools, water and a wet towel do the trick.
As is always the case with trends, brands have come up with all kinds of interpretations in addition to the classic look.
For example, if you wish, you can buy a straw braided radish bag or a small shoulder bag instead.
At the same time, it is worth remembering that a classic straw bag will never go out of fashion, but a straw griddle will.
But what is a classic straw bag?
Such a bag woven from straw, which resembles a basket in its style, is open at the top and has short handles, also made of straw, has been considered classic for centuries.
